Turtlesim Ball Tracking System

The idea is a robot (turtlesim) that follows a ball from a virtual camera

System build:

Camera Node: 
responsible for creating frames with the help of the numpy framework i was able to generate frames that opencv can work with 

Ball Detection Node:
The Node was responsible to subscribe to Camera Node and publish the ball location every given moment

Control robot node:
The Node was responsible to subscribe to the ball location and subscribe to the robot pose and publish to the cmd_vel the velocity that the robot should have in order to steer towards the ball 


Information about the probject 
The camera was created with opencv framework

The ball detection was possible with color detection  and contours detection. (thats how i detect the ball like contour)

The robot control system was PID controller calculating the error and adjusting respectfully to reach the ball




How to run: 
```bash
chmod +x build_and_run.sh
./build_and_run.sh
```
How to develop:
```
Use the devcontainer oepn in Vscode and Build with devcontainer extention 
```
How to run tests:
```
Inside the devcontainer just use .vscode/tasks
assign a beautiful shortcut to run the tests easily
```
```bash

cd ./ros2_ws/src/ball_tracking_system
python3 -m pytest -m unit
```







